{
  "title": "Floods, Faults & Firestorms:",
  "body": "<html><body><div id=\"block-ti-west-content\">\n<article>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div class=\"container container--max-width paragraph paragraph--type--text paragraph--type--text--bleed paragraph--view-mode--default\">\n<div><div class=\"hero__container hero__container--small hero__container--no-image\" data-hero-container=\"\"><div class=\"container container--max-width\"><div class=\"hero__text-container hero__text-container--center hero__text-container__small\"><h1 class=\"u-font-family-secondary hero__title\">Floods, Faults &amp; Firestorms: <br/>Wildfire, Earthquake and Flood Risk in the US</h1></div></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div class=\"container container--max-width paragraph paragraph--type--text paragraph--view-mode--default\">\n<div><p>Wildfire, earthquake, and flood risks aren’t limited to specific regions, they are increasingly nationwide concerns. Unpack shifting risk zones, widespread misconceptions, and why many consumers remain underinsured. Explore how population shifts, aging infrastructure, and climate trends are transforming exposure across the U.S. Learn about insurer adaptations, new coverage options, and practical agent strategies to reduce E&amp;O exposure and improve client conversations. No matter where you are, these disasters are closer to home than you might think.</p><table style=\"font-size:inherit;margin:32px 0;width:100%;\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"padding-right:40px;vertical-align:top;\"><strong>Pricing</strong><br/>$49.00*</td><td style=\"vertical-align:top;\"><strong>Webinar Duration</strong><br/>60 minutes</td><td style=\"vertical-align:top;\"><strong>CE Requirements</strong><br/><a href=\"https://web.theinstitutes.org/ceu/state-requirements\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Verify your state and license CE requirements</a></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div class=\"container container--max-width paragraph paragraph--type--text paragraph--view-mode--default\">\n<div><section class=\